Mobiles.LongDescription: A rainbow colored fish swims quickly through the water here.
Mobiles.Description: Light glints beautifully off its scales as it glides gracefully throughthe water.  Its tail moves gently back and forth to guide it, and its gillsmove in and out in pulsating waves, physical evidence that the fish stillbreathes (You could probably have assumed this fact anyway).

Mobiles.LongDescription: A silver backed fish swims quickly through the water.
Mobiles.Description: THis fish glints with the brightest flashes of silver as it streaksthrough the clear, crisp water with a subtle swish of its tail.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A robed dockworker moves carefully about the docks here.
A villager walks pensively here, face hidden by his brown robes.
A villager stands here silently, regarding you quizzically.
Mobiles.Description: The villager seems very in place here, at one with the silence andwhirlwind of emotions that pass through the air and the streets of Cove.His demeanor of silence is not unusual in this environment, as it would bein another time or place.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The seeress of Cove sits here, mumbling unintelligibly.
Mobiles.Description: The wrinkles on her face and hands betray the age that was undeterminablesimply by looking into her eyes.  Deep blue pools of radiance gaze out fromthose pale sockets, penetrating and fixating you at the same time.  Her hairhas been tightly pulled back over her head with a thin, purple sash, itscolor matching the robes that float heavily over her body.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A swarthy fisherman walks slowly through the streets here.
Mobiles.Description: You are surprised when this man makes eye contact with you, unlike mostof the other citizens of this small village.  His eyes glint a deep darkblue, blue that matches the waters where he plies his trade.  Bulgingmuscles jut out from underneath the trimming on his tunic, naturally tonedfrom many hours of work on the ships and on the lines.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A child lies in a heap here, obviously sick and shivering.
Mobiles.Description: His hair is matted against his forehead, a tribute to the battle thatrages in his insides, a battle against the one thing that most people fear,not death or loss from battle, but the insideous clutches of a disease thateats at your innards, convulsing them into a bloody pulp that showsexternally only as a series of faint bruises.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A woodland squirrel has wandered into town here.
Mobiles.Description: Hair bristles up the back of this little furry animal, a little thingthat seems to have gotten lost somewhere during the course of itswanderings.  It looks cautiously at you with its beady black eyes, curiosityobviously overcoming his desire to run away.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A silent bird sits on the tree branches here, pensively mute.
A man sits on the ground cross legged, lost in his own reverie.
Mobiles.Description: The faintest shade of today's facial hair growth is evident along thisman's gaunt chin and cheeks, tight skin that is pulled taut over the bonesof his skull.  In fact, you can see just how skinny this man is by the looseway his clothes hang on his body.  His eyes seem glazed over with thatdistant stare of one who does not live in the present, you wonder if perhapshis man has forgotten to eat at some point in his sad existence.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A curious fish with three spindly tails swims gracefully here.
Mobiles.Description: Light flashes off this fish's gills and scales as it glides effortlesslythrough the water, using its three tails for balance, and propulsion.  Likemost fish, it does not appear to be very intelligent, its black beady eyesglazed over in the depths of the water.

Mobiles.LongDescription: The Seeker of Truth stands here, resplendent in its fine robes.
Mobiles.Description: Long flowing whiskers frame his old and wizened face, giving him the lookof age old perfection and virtue.  On second thought however, you realizethat the Seeker may not be a man after all, on third thought, you realizeyou have no chance in hell of determining its sex, short of feeling itscrotch.  In any case, he exudes virtue, and you cannot help but feel guiltyat his presence.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A penitent man lies prone on the ground here, praying.
Mobiles.Description: His form fades in and out, solid then transparent.  It is almost as ifthis man is on the cusp of the world, his existence in the balance.  It alsomay be his ascendence into a higher plane, as you have heard avatars advanceto.  In any case, he is ethereal in appearance, and frankly, it's a littlefrightening.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A wild novena bird sits in the treetops here, chirping madly.
Mobiles.Description: It chirps madly and with reckless abandon, a seemingly insane look on itsblue and red striped face.  It is difficult to determine just why you thinkthis bird has lost its marbled, but it just doesn't seem right, it's alittle too frisky.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Shadra the wizened alchemist of Cove waits patiently here.
Mobiles.Description: Her wrinkled face looks back at you with tistase as she mixes her herbsand other foreign substances.  Although she appears dour and quiteunintelligible, you have the feeling that she possesses great intelligence.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Patric the master crystal artist of Cove sits behind the counter here.
Mobiles.Description: He is a short man, facial hair hanging roughly over his face.  Hisfeatures are indelicate to say the least, but as you watch him work, yourealize the brilliant elegance of his fingers, of his arms, and the way hemolds crystals into the forms that he desires.  He looks up quietly, smileswarmly, and goes back to work.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A mockingbird flits to and fro, singing merrily.
A woman clad in white floats serenely over the water here.
Mobiles.Description: Her diaphanous clothes flow over her body gently as she stands quietly inthe center of the lake.  She seems to float, to dance and flicker over theslightly rippling surface, oblivious of all that she sees around her.Except you of course, who she smiles at benevolently.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Atsu, master scribe of Cove sits at his desk writing.
Mobiles.Description: His back is hunched over from countless years of sitting at his desk, yethis eyes seem focused, and more importantly, intelligent.  His stares up atyou from beneath his droopy eyelids and bushy eyebrows, his wizened facefrowns for a moment, then brightens when he hears the jingle of coins inyour pocket.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An elder wise one steps out of the diamond shaped light.
Mobiles.Description: A beard graces this wizened man's face, long and flowing white thatreaches down to his waist.  His benevolent smile does not say much abouthim, except that over the years, not even wisdom can preserve teeth withoutproper dental hygiene.

Mobiles.LongDescription: Argent, the shipwright of Cove, stands here haughtily.
Mobiles.Description: A big burly man stands in front of you, tattoos dotting his rippling armsand otherwise strong body.  A light growth of beard covers his chin,covering the acne problems that he has had most of his life.  However, yousee that he has a keen eye for boats, as he expertly lashes together piecesof wood with polished reed in order to form a rudimentary but practicalraft.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A serpentine, glittering blue dragon eyes you hungrily.
Mobiles.Description: It glares at you with menacing eyes, slightly slanted gold eyes placedjust above facial whiskers that almost make the dragon look wise.  His bodycurls all about the chamber, a long thin snakelike thing that is covered inshiny blue scales.  The glittering obviously comes from the multitude ofgems that are encrusted within those scales.

Mobiles.LongDescription: An ancient, glittering bronze dragon glares at you here.
Mobiles.Description: It glares at you with menacing eyes, slightly slanted gold eyes placedjust above facial whiskers that almost make the dragon look wise.  His bodycurls all about the chamber, a long thin snakelike thing that is covered inshiny bronze scales.  The glittering obviously comes from the multitude ofgems that are encrusted within those scales.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beautiful liquid-eyed fawn grazes here.
Mobiles.Description: Small white spots dot this beautiful deer's back, her antlerless headperfectly created.  It is small and cute though, it looks at you with aninnocence bred by years of easy life.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A proud necked doe stands here with her family.
Mobiles.Description: If you were a deer, you would be all over this gorgeously constructeddoe.  Beautiful eyes and fine rippling muscles underneath its perfectly madeskin make it the virtual paragon of all does, beautiful and innocent in thisland of Cove.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A gracefully powerful deer stands here.
Mobiles.Description: Majestic is the only word you can use to describe this antlered deer.His antlers form a basket of bone above its head, reaching high up above himin this primordial salute to the powers that be.  He looks ratherdefensively at you, his rippling muscles tensing in the event that youattack his family.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of red light flashes towards you here.
Mobiles.Description: Pure brilliance of red fire flares back into your eyes.  You cannot stareinto its depths for very much longer, lest you find yourself blind, andsaneless.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of orange light flashes towards you here.
Mobiles.Description: At first you are reminded of a fruit, but that is probably just becauseof the sheer power of the orange color.  There is nothing citrusy about thelight though: it is a burning, tearing orange harsher than an acid.  Theclosest comparison is to the brilliant feathers of a delila bird.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of yellow light flashes towards you here.
Mobiles.Description: Yellow is the color of the sun, the color of the imaginary sunflowersthat sprout in your imaginary ravings, the color your imaginary friend wearsand the color of the dots that you try to blink out of your eyes as you lookinto the LIGHT.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of blue light flashes through the air here.
Mobiles.Description: Blue as the deepest ocean, but blazing with the intensity of a hundredkatsi bug lanterns that have been placed about like the Festival of Moons.It is amazing, brilliant, a beautiful sight to behold.  Unfortunately, it ismaking you blind, so you had better look away soon.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of green light flashes at you here.
Mobiles.Description: Although you have seen green seeded deeply in evil before, this lighttranscends your previous experiences.  It is a disgusting green, sewage-likeimpurity assaulting your senses.  Your stomach roils in disgust.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of indigo light streaks through the air here.
Mobiles.Description: Previously, indigo was always an amorphous idea - a shade, indeterminate,between blue and purple without being truly either.  Indigo was always theamorphous area between right and wrong, shade but neither shadow nor light.Now, however, in the scintillating glare of this room, you know indigo.  Thelight is so bright, it seems to burn through your eyelids, etching the coloron your eyes, and certainly not soothing your offended ocular nerves.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A beam of violet light flashes towards you here.
Mobiles.Description: It's purple!  Why does everyone call it violet?  It's passionate, poutypurple light, brighter than even the most flowery and lurid of purple prose.The light pulsates with a life that you might previously have assumed wasreserved for corporeal beings.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A man in a brightly flowered tunic offers sell you some fruit, almost free!
A three striped tern is perched on a branch high overhead.
A spotted jin bird flutters in the air here.
A tinseled mothbird hovers happily in the air here.
A hunch backed old man sits here reading.
Mobiles.Description: His back hunched over permanently from too many years of reading, thiseyes squinted from the lack of light.  He doesn't look like a very imposingfigure.  Grey hair that has more than halfway fallen out, baggy skin thatbegs to be tucked in.  He is a veritable mess, soggy and old.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A silver scaled chill fish glids through the water here.
Mobiles.Description: Light glints beautifully off its scales as it glides gracefully throughthe water.  Its tail moves gently back and forth to guide it, and its gillsmove in and out in pulsating waves, physical evidence that the fish stillbreathes (You could probably have assumed this fact anyway).

Mobiles.LongDescription: The quiet soul of a villager paces the village here.

Rooms.RoomDescription: With a sudden rush and a gurgle of lost air, you find yourself in a smallriver inlet that is shaded by the boughs of forest trees that overhang thewater.  The flow of the water is from the east, a calm and collected poolthat has lost much of its force since its inception somewhere off in themountains.  Small wildlife flits about here, insects mostly, buzzing aroundin the still of the river.  There is a somewhat peculiar smell in the air, afaint acrid odor that reminds you of a pipe that has been burning a fewhours too long.

The forested area suddenly gives way to clear banks complete with warmand soft looking grass.  It is a wonder you did not notice the forestopening up before, it is that dramatic of a change.  The grass gives you asense of closure, or maybe it's not really the grass alone.  It is the entiresense of ARRIVING somewhere, of finally reaching the end of a long soughtdestination.  Maybe you were never looking for this place, maybe you wereonly looking for the next step of a long sequence of meaningless events inlife.  But you are here, and it feels...  Right.

The calm inlet flows steadily inwards somewhere.  Just as before when youdid not notice the forest clearing, you did not notice the mountain rangesthat now slam out of the ground to frame the grass and trees that surroundthe water.  They raise themselves majestically, craggy peaks not unscalable,but certainly a difficult traverse for unprepared travelers.  The moreinviting path of the river leads off to the east here, twisting and turningas only rivers can do.

You have arrived at the end of the brilliantly lighted path whose glarehas been an assault on your optic senses.  A chest, woven of brilliant beamsof light, rests on the ground here, apparently locked.  It is remarkable youcan see the chest at all, with all the brilliant lights in your eyes.

You find yourself twising and turning together with the winding of theriver, feeling at one with the medium through which you travel.  It is acomfortable feeling of fluidity, flexibility, that makes you want to believethat you can do anything, go anywhere, conquer any unforeseen fear.  Themountains that rise up beyond the clearings of the river banks are hardly adistraction as the newfound internal nirvana you have found focuses on theswirls and eddies in the water, and on the river ahead and behind.

The calm inlet runs north and south here, a smooth flowing river thatglistens in the shade of the mountains that rear up just beyond its banks.It has the color of the clearest glass, simply put, absolutely no color atall.  Splashes of water spray up from beneath your feet, grabbing flickersof light that have filtered down into the river valley.  Just to the southof here, the river runs under a massive construct of crystal, its impossibleto make out exactly what it is though.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n steps onto the glittering surface of the topaz docks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n leaves the docks to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand at a pair of dry docks that lie at the foot of what appears tobe a small village.  The mechanisms that allow ships to come clean out ofthe water are not visible here, hidden by the shimmering structure of topazthat the docks are made out of.  Water flows lazily underneath the dock,from some upriver source in the mountains.  Stray light manages to streak inover the surrounding mountains, blinking and reflecting off the topaz.  Asmall road made from crushed marble runs off to the east here, off into agrove of trees and small buildings.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The crashing footsteps of $n temporarily disrupt your pure calm.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wind whispers quietly as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Marble crushes gently underneath your feet as you tread upon the paththat it marks.  It seems blissfully quiet here, the only sounds are those ofthe nearby rushing water, and the swaying of leaves in the valley wind.  Asyou look down the length of the path to the east, it seems to shimmer andcoalesce a short ways in the distance, like the rays of light that cloudyour vision when you have been looking at the sun too long and colors startto dance in the corners of your eyes.  To the north of here is a smallbuilding, a sign hanging firmly from black metal spoors depicts a ship withgull winged sails and sleek hull.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The crashing footsteps of $n temporarily disrupt your pure calm.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wind whispers quietly as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The path through town known as Tranquility to the natives intersectsanother 'street' here that heads off to the south through a copse of trees.A blissful quiet has washed over you since you stepped onto Tranquility, ahumbling calm that emanates from the marble beneath your feet, from the airthat you are breathing, even from the very mixture of shadow and light thatflows down from the mountains.  Just to the north of here is a small home,decorated on the outside as if the owner did not have a care in the worldand probably not all that much contact with the world.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The crashing footsteps of $n temporarily disrupt your pure calm.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wind whispers quietly as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: A warm hush fills the air here, a serene quiet that does not feel likethe calm before the storm, does not feel like the forest holding its breathas fire passes its branches, does not feel like the uneasy silence that twopeople starting to fall in love have.  It is simply bliss, a soothingambience that washes over you as you walk down the crushed marble street andpast the doors of the home to the south of you.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The crashing footsteps of $n temporarily disrupt your pure calm.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wind whispers quietly as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Tranquility is here.  Tranquility is now.  The inner peace that you feelas you step across the crushed marble path would be startling, if you didn'tfeel so much at ease with yourself.  It is difficult to say exactly wherethe feeling comes from, the air, the trees, the cold wind that blows downfrom the mountains that frame the valley?  Or maybe it is just you, finallyfeeling that what you are doing now is not just preparation for some blindfuture, not living for tomorrow anymore, understanding that today is not aprelude to the next day, but rather the epilogue to yesterday, and thestories of now.  On a lighter note, a building stands to the north, a smallsign with a flickering blue flame on it hangs loosely above the entry door.Off to the south runs another street, one that emanates a completelydifferent set of emotions.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The crashing footsteps of $n temporarily disrupt your pure calm.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The wind whispers quietly as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The crushed marble path continues to the east and west here, a blazonwhite swath of rock in the middle of an otherwise very quaint village.There is a feeling of easy bliss in the air here, a complete and trueharmony with everything that spins and flies and roams the world here.  Atanother time, the silence and stillness of the area would be troublesome,disconcerting.  But it just feels right somehow, as if this little villagewere always meant to be permanently isolated from the world that liesbeyond.  A small cottage stands to the south here, doors open and welcome tovisitors.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n crashes into view, obviously flustered.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n leaves to the $T, leaving you to your reverie.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Tranquility suddenly comes to an end here, not in a calamitous roar orthe physical end of the street.  No, it is the unimposing tinkling ofbells that wafts through the air from the north.  It would not seem to bethe ruiner of peace and harmony, but nevertheless, it does not quite fit, ananomaly that the mountain valley village of Cove does not cope with well.In any case, a path leads off to the north where you can see a lonesomebuilding glimmering in the ambient light.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The brush parts as $n enters the garden path.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n's footsteps fade away to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: All about you, flowers and other flora sprout about, encasing the paththat you walk on in a virtual wall of greens, reds, and yellows.  Up ahead ashort distance, you can make out a small building, hut would be moreaccurate.  Small windows peek out from behind stray leaves, shuttered closedwith thick slabs of deep black wood.  The air around the building seems toshimmer with a faint light, a golden hum that encapsulates whatever newadventure you will find inside.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n pushes $s way past velvet drapes into the room.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n ducks his head and leaves the Prophecy.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand in a chamber that is awash with the glow of a million stars, amillion pinprick points of light that come together, and as one, are brightenough to blind.  Which leads you to wonder what stars are doing inside abuilding.  A table covered with a royal purple cloth rests near the farwall, a chair of matching wood resting behind it.  On the table rests a setof cards, and a pair of bracelets crafted from immolated steel.

Naturally lit by the sun that streams through the bamboo fronds tiedtogether as a makeshift roof, this home is both cool and comfy.  Completelyunfurnished save for a cushion in the corner that must function as a bed,the straw and grass that comprise this home allow in ample light and seabreeze.  The sound of ocean waves crashing on the nearby docks float intothis home unhampered and wild.

Where the interior walls of this building should be are instead massiverows of crystals that seem to grow out of the ground you walk on.  Brillianthues of blue and pink highlight the room, a myriad of colors that sends alikewise set of emotions running though your mind.  A man sits towards theback of the room on his chair, crafting a much smaller crystal in his hand.Rumor has it that Cove produces magical crystals which have special effects,perhaps you should try one out.

You stand in a small hut that is loosely decorated with a variety ofgrass made entrapments and glowing candles.  Bags of herbs and other scentshang from thin rope which in turn, dangle from thin wooden branch beams thatarc gracefully with the ceiling.  A few pieces of furniture dot the roomhere, but otherwise, the hut seems pretty barren and uninviting.

You stand in a small hut that is loosely decorated with a variety ofgrass made entrapments and glowing candles.  Bags of herbs and other scentshang from thin rope which in turn, dangle from thin wooden branch beams thatarc gracefully with the ceiling.  A few pieces of furniture dot the roomhere, but otherwise, the hut seems pretty barren and uninviting.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n mumbles penitently as $e walks nearby.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n leaves passively to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand on a well shaded street that curves slightly to the east as youwalk down its north south bearing.  Even more than anything you can see,hear, or touch, is the pervading feeling that this is a street meant for thepious, for the penitent man who wishes to walk in the light of reason andhumility.  The crunch of the marble beneath your feet and the crackle ofswaying brown leaves betrays the overwhelming repentance at your own pridethat is marked by the silence that you bear.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n mumbles penitently as $e walks nearby.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n slips quietly to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: There are times when you think that everything in the world is yours, inthe palm of your hand, to grab, to hold, and to cherish like a fine appleblossom that has bloomed when everything else is stagnant and brown.  Andwhen that time comes, you feel happy, and tend to forget about the thingsthat have happened in your existence.  Imagine you have found that appleblossom one day, and the next day, a storm hits and cracks that apple tree.Imagine the despair that you feel upon the realization that no more appleblossoms will bloom from its limbs, and that you clutch, in vain, a singleblossom that will wither, die, a memory that will have to suffice as foodfor your pride and happiness.  Imagine this, and you know the feeling thatraces through your heart at this instant, a heaviness that you will not besorry to leave behind.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Black light pours over $n as $e enters the alchemy.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n is chased from the alchemy by black light.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You find yourself standing in a room awash in black light.  It isn't theodd black light that you are used to, purple lantern shade over a normalflame, but instead, a light that seems to suck out the shadows from everycrack and crevice in the walls and floor.  Bags of herbs, spices, and otheresoterica hang from thin strands of twine attached to the ceiling.  A thickmat of dull green grass grows on the floor of the shop here, an oddity thatmatches the strangeness of the store.

You stand in a small shady home that smells of earth, moss, and othernatural aromas.  The ceiling of the house is actually a thick interleavingof branches and leaves that form a canopy, impenetrable by water and wind.Small lanterns, carefully shuttered rest in sconces all around the room,casting a soft white glow across the sparse furnishings here.  A desk, and abed are all that is here, apparently the desk doubles as a dining table, asa variety of cheeses and wine sits on the table.

You stand in a small chamber that is dominated by a number of shutteredlanterns that cast their glow across the room.  A counter towards the backhas been erected, where a man stands, gruff looking and not too hard atwork.  Numerous massive stuffed fish hang from the walls, beautiful catchesthat presumably come from the ocean to the west.  A pad of paper and quillpen rest on the hard wood counter, ostensibly for you to draw up your shipspecifications and desires.  Remember, this isn't called the pithyshipwright for nothing.

After your almost certain death has passed, you find yourself in averitable rock garden.  Boulders and chunks of sandstone, limestone, andgranite litter the area, a perversely diversified bunch of geologicalstructures, all which a minute ago had been intent on shattering your skull.The skeleton that lies in the corner of the gully doesn't do much for yourconfidence either.  You realize suddenly, that perfectly smooth cliffs linethe gully, you doubt you could get out if you tried.

Bright light shimmers all about you, flashing different colors all aroundyour head and mind.  It is a cacophony of visual sound, a powerfularrangement of the spectrum that leaves you gripping for your sanity.  It isimpossible to tell where you stand or where you are headed, it is all verychaotic.
You have obviously told a lie somewhere before.  If you have the time tobe reading this room description, you are a brave soul indeed.

You stand at the end of Honesty, a metaphor that is aptly fitted to thistime in the world of deception, hate, and misery.  Small doors lead to theeast, north, and west, hopefully, you have told the truth by now, and willknow which doors leads the way to fulfillment, and which way will make youstop breathing (ha ha ha).  The doors are unmarked slabs of solid oak,polished prettily but ungaudily.  A small blue flame lantern flickersuneasily at the side of each door, expectant of your next move.

What is the truth?  Is it not simply the comprehension of what isperceived and felt?  Is it not the way ideas and facts flow together to formwhat is WANTED, and not what is actually present?  It is a difficultquestion to be sure, but it is a question that somehow demands to beanswered as you pace carefully down the emerald lined street.  Like asmith's hammer rocking against the interior of your skull, you feel thispulsating need to know the truth, to give the truth, and breathe the truth.Sunlight smashes down onto your face, and the needs becomes more pressing.

There is a crisp brittle quality to the air here, a feeling of completeand utter dichotomy, right and wrong, good and evil.  Somehow it leaves yourchest heaving for air, as you struggle to grasp that seed inside ofyourself, that little seed that causes people to be deceptive, to hurt, tofind it in themselves to lie, cheat, and steal.  You fear that if you do notyank that little festering seed out soon, something BAD might happen.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: A small path leads through the forest here, a padded swath of dirt thatwinds its way through tall, towering aspen trees.  Cones have fallen to theground, and a thick mat of grass covers the area not already entranced bytrees.  Here and there, you can see the wildlife peeking out at you withoutpretension, oblivious to the madness and killing that people often bringwith them.  Through the slats between trees and the light filtering downinto the forest, you can see that you can head either north or east here.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The forest trail quickly takes a slope downwards here, emptying out intoa ravine that is surrounded by aspen trees that still somehow grow straightinto the air despite the angled terrain of the land.  The ravine runs northto south, making it very difficult to traverse the thick forest to eitherthe east or west.  In any case, the sounds of animals in the forest and theother sounds of nature are unpredictable, distractions from negotiating theterrain.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The forest trail runs down into a deep ravine here, cutting across thegrain of the landscape at a northeast angle.  Aspen trees grow from thesides of the slopes, angling upwards precariously.  The footing here is abit treacherous, small bits of rocky rubble have come to replace the softmats of verdant grass that once inhabited the area beneath the trees.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You find yourself in the bottom layer of the forest ravine, slopesreaching high up on either side of you.  Aspen trees grow at strange angleson those slopes, effectively blocking much of the sun that dares to filterdown into the area.  The ground up ahead is damp with moisture, the normallyrocky ground long since turned to mud.  Somewhere off to the north, youthink you can hear the sounds of running water.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n's feet splash in the water as he climbs over the brook.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n follows the curve of the brook to the $T, and disappears from view.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The forest ravine turns perpendicularly here, a sharp turn that you tendto think appears unnatural.  The entire scene is like a picture show, scenesflashing by as the sunn appears then disappears behind trees and clouds upahead.  Shadows on the ground play across the joyful meandering of ababbling brook that runs through the ravine here.  It gurgles playfully tothe east and south, as does the ravine itself.  Animals graze on theoccasional moss and lichen that you see growing beneath the trees, obliviousof the danger that a leveling adventurer such as yourself possesses.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n's feet splash in the water as he climbs over the brook.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n follows the curve of the brook to the $T, and disappears from view.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand in a deep forest ravine, towering aspen trees parting to eitherside of you.  The ground here is muddy, perhaps it has to do with theperiodic flooding of the small stream that flows through the ravine.  Theslopes that define the ravine allow you to head north or east or south here,more forest in every direction that you look.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Finally, you appear to be travelling upwards again, and out of the deepforest ravine.  Actually, come to think about it, the trees are thinning outas well, and you think you can make out the end/edge of the forest up ahead.The jutting and snow capped bare peak of a towering mountain shows itselfbetween two trees that you walk past, confirming your suspicions.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n scrambles his way towards you over the ravine rocks.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n assures his footing and scurries off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomName: At the foot of a mountain trail
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand at the foot of a mountain trail, a small path that cuts throughthe aspen trees and heads upwards to destinations unknown.  A small trailalso leads off to the west and through the forest ravine.  It is verypeaceful here, and if not for all the mosquitos and other small crittersflitting about, you could probably stay here forever.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n trudges into sight on the mountain trail.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n checks $s footing and leaves $T on the trail.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The mountain trail continues onwards here, a thin five foot wide paththat is framed on one side by towering aspen trees and on the other by asteep cliff face that ends in a pile of rubble some 200 feet below.  Thesmell of pine needles in the air is overpowering, and the air has a crisp,dry quality to it.  It makes breathing both easier, and more difficult, butnevertheless, it feels peaceful here, quiet.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n trudges into sight on the mountain trail.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n checks $s footing and leaves $T on the trail.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The mountain trail continues its ascent (or descent, depending on whichway you want to look at it) here.  The trail clings to the side of themountain, framed on one side by the plethora of aspen trees, and on theother by a cliff.  It isn't recommended that you try descending the cliff,its a long way down to be sure, and you don't think you'd be able to getback up if you tried.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n trudges into sight on the mountain trail.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n checks $s footing and leaves $T on the trail.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The mountain trail winds its way slowly around the sides of the mountain,a path five feet wide and precariously unsupported on the side.  Theoverpowering scent of pine needles fills the air, massive aspen treesreaching straight for the sky, with lesser cousins clinging to the nap ofthe earth.  The trail leads off to the north, where you think you can makeout the faint sounds of water running.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n interrupts your serenity and walks into the clearing.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The lake is a little quiet as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You stand in a quiet shelter high up on the slopes of the mountains.Snow falls gently around the edges of the lake, melting almost as soon asthey touch the ground.  The water itself is perfectly clear, the reflectionof the sky, trees, and mountains virtual twins to their real life brethren.Soft bladed green grass pads the shores of the lake, a flowing green matthat eases the pain in your feet and body.  A small trail winds its waysouth out of the clearing and away from the lake here.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n appears through the mists of Spirituality.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The mists part as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Although the street is made from the same crushed marble as Tranquility,from which it branches off from, the sensations you get from the wavingtrees, the small buildings, and the air itself, is completely different.You feel a sense of, not belonging here, a if your soul is missing a partthat material possessions and equipment and gold cannot make up.  It is oddthat the primal sensations you feel quite easily dominate any physicalsensations you receive.  You barely notice the beautiful craggy mountainsthat frame Cove, or the faint smell of sea water washing in from the coast.

Rooms.EnterMsg: $n appears through the mists of Spirituality.
Rooms.ExitMsg: The mists part as $n leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: The sense of loneliness and unfulfillment that you feel seems foreign inthis place, nestled in among the mountains.  It seems that being alone wouldnot matter in a place like this.  But maybe it isn't exactly what you arefeeling, this sense that you are missing something.  Maybe that missingsomething is off to the west, where a small path made from colorful mosaicscurls away from the road.  More likely though, it can be found in thestained glass chapel that stands just to the south of here.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Bells chime deeply as $n enters the chapel.
Rooms.ExitMsg: Bells jingle lightly as $n leaves $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: If it weren't for the stained glass that so elegantly graces this room'swalls and ceiling, it would look like any other home in Cove.  Small, madefrom fresh wood, and with rows and rows of benches in front of an altar.Apparently, this is the chapel of Cove.  The air is a bit musty here, as ifpeople do not frequent this building very often.  A small ladder leadsupwards here, the destination unknown and darkened.

You stand on a colorful mosaic path that does not seem to retain any ofthe dirt or mud that you thought you left on it.  Consequently, it sparkleslike the midday sun as it curls away from the wall of the chapel, and into agrove of tall, thin trees whose leaves have turned yellow in anticipation ofwinter festivities.  The mosaic pattern itself is pretty boring, or at leastyou thought it was until you realized that you had been staring at it forminutes, hypnotizing isn't it?

The mosaic path continues to the east and south here, a flowing,mezmerizing pattern that takes your time up as you stand there and examineit.  A small well stands to the south, among a small clearing in the treesthat you are currently walking through.  It seems a bit out of place off inthe corner of nowhere, but then again, things in Cove are never as they seemare they?

The path opens up into a forest clearing that has been built around acircle of perfectly cut granite.  In the center of the circle, elevatedslightly by terraced steps leading up to it, is a well made from stone.  Asmall bucket hangs above the well, suspended with a rope that has beendraped across the end of the well and anchored to a small metal pin.  Theforest is thick here, inpenetrable to be exact.

You stand in a circular room, panelled with loosely fitting pieces ofwood that have been crafted from the cross section of trees that surroundCove.  Windows have been cut into the walls, clear glass that allows you tolook out onto the forest to the west, south, and east, and the village ofCove to the north.  Small candles light the room, flickerless and scentless.A small ladder allows you to go back to the main level of the chapel.

Flashes of light scream across your field of vision, a myriad offantastic colors that daze, and blind you.  It is impossible to see whereyou are going in this wash of colors, in fact, it is impossible to see evenwhere you stand.  Occasionally, a beam of light careens towards you, and theinnate sense that you possess tells you that they are dangerous, and youmight be in serious trouble here.

Despite the apparent clarity of the water when looking at it from upabove, the water in the quiet mountain lake is surprisingly murky, or"heavy" as some scribes like to call it.  Meaning the density of the wateris such that light is unable to penetrate it at depths of more than tenfeet.  In any case, even in the darkness, you can see the faint outline ofwhite pillars far below.  Only the strongest of swimmers would be able toreach that point more than 100 feet deep, and truth be told, you areprobably not one of them.  Besides, the water from the glacial run offs isbitterly cold, and you had probably get out of the lake before the chillssets in.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The trees hum quietly as $n walks near.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n's footsteps echo on the marble as $e leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Birds chirp in perfect intervals as you walk past them, a beautifulsymphony of nature that flows easily and wraps itself in your ears, sight,and heart.  Trees sway listlessly to the music, the wind seems to want toplay a part as well, whipping around your feet whenever the occasion callsfor it.  The marble underneath your feet crunches slightly as you pressagainst it with the soles of your feet, slightly springy but certainlycomfortable.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The trees hum quietly as $n walks near.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n's footsteps echo on the marble as $e leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Harmony flows all about you in this serene but somehow ebullient street.The forest erupts with life around you, a cascade of color and sound thatalthough a definite contrast to the wafting silence of Tranquility that youhave left behind, altogether as pleasant.  Birds flit to and fro as theyprance their innate dance with each other, and random rainbows flit acrossthe edges of your vision as you take in the panorama.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The trees hum quietly as $n walks near.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n's footsteps echo on the marble as $e leaves to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: You have reached an abrupt end to the marble street internally calledHarmony.  It is strange, somehow you had felt that Harmony's end would besmoother, a more lucient transition into something else, something bettermaybe.  Instead, the road looks as if it were unfinished, aspen trees thattower up into the sky taking over where it leaves off.  In any case, a pathleads off into the forest to the east, a small dirt trail that winds its waybetween tree trunks.

And then there was light!  It crashes down upon you like a smith's hammerto the anvil, heavy light, blinding light, powerful light that makes youwince in its splendor and gape at the splashes of color that now dot yourarmor, your weapon, your clothes.  The path you walk on is more brilliantthen any gem-encrusted sceptre or palace you have ever seen.  Beautyincarnate.

Have you seen the colors of the rainbow today?  Have you seen it washingover your face like a hail of confetti on the day of a grand parade?  Haveyou wiped the sparkles, flashes of brightness out of your eyes yet?  Can yousee the ribbon like path that you walk on in oblivious believing?  Searinglight crashes into your questions and disperses them into a million shardsof brilliance, fleeing to the corners of the sphere, fleeing from your mindand presence.

Various colors of the spectrum flow over you and sparkle your vision asyou stand upon a narrow band of solidified light.  The air seems to shimmerand spiral upwards counterclockwise, whirling with a speed that dizzies thesenses.  The path that you walk on continues off to the north and west here,ribbon and snake like in its convolutions and turns and twists.

You stand amidst the chapel's thick wooden rafters, the musty smell uphere overpowering.  Light filters through a small window in the north wallthat allows you to see the street to the north of the chapel, but littleelse.  The window is cracked and unkempt, cobwebs creeping up on itscorners.  Stuffed away in the corner of the room, balanced at theintersection of 2 rafters, is a sturdy iron chest, a shiny new lock in itscenter.

Rooms.EnterMsg: Bells chime deeply as $n enters the chapel.
Rooms.ExitMsg: Bells jingle lightly as $n leaves $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: If it weren't for the stained glass that so elegantly graces this room'swalls and ceiling, it would look like any other home in Cove.  Small, madefrom fresh wood, and with rows and rows of benches in front of an altar.Apparently, this is the chapel of Cove.  The air is a bit musty here, as ifpeople do not frequent this building very often.  A small ladder leadsupwards here, the destination unknown and darkened.

You stand amidst the chapel's thick wooden rafters, the musty smell uphere overpowering.  Light filters through a small window in the north wallthat allows you to see the street to the north of the chapel, but littleelse.  The window is cracked and unkempt, cobwebs creeping up on itscorners.  Stuffed away in the corner of the room, balanced at theintersection of 2 rafters, is a sturdy iron chest, a shiny new lock in itscenter.
Fool, Honesty takes its tolls.  I seriously doubt if you have time toread this room description, if you are, then you will be dead shortly.

You have arrived in a smll chamber bathed in green sunlight.  It filterson down through a canopy of leaves overhead, a trees branches reaching overyour head and to the doorway.  In the center of the room, a brilliantdiamond shaped efervesence beams in on itself, something in its centerseemingly attracting the light.  As you stare closer, you realize thatperhaps it is a man, a woman, a something.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The brass bell rings loudly as $n enters.
Rooms.RoomDescription: A magical land of paradise and respite, birds fly lovingly up above, thesun shines all day in a beautiful microcosm of heaven.  Waters lap at thenearby shores with calming regularity.  Trees sway gently in the seabreezes,giving you shade to rest in should you feel weary, a place to relaxyourself, and be at one with the world.  What is even more important aboutthis place of rest is that it has free food!

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: It is the wonderful land of paradise, or as close to paradise as you canget.  (In fact, Paradiso is only one step to the south, but you didn't hearthat from me) Water here is beautiful, an ocean of enormous magnitude ,greatest magnitude to be precise.  Whoa, this just in, you love it here.Film at 11.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Waters lap up on the nearby shore, a vast expanse of ocean that stretchesfor as far as you can see.  The isle itself is wonder enough for you though,perfect calm and loving serenity are the emotions evoked here, a wonderfulland where you can rest your troubles from the world, as heroes of long pasthave supposedly done.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Water rolls up onto the shore here, crystal clear water that appears andsmells drinkable despite the vast ocean expanse it comes from.  The islethat you stand on is a beautiful complement to the clear waters, trees swayin the midday sun ( it always appears to be midday here), the grass is acushioned mattress beneath your feet (or derrierre, depending on what you'redoing right now).  Birds soar high above you, not those merry chirping birdsyou have grown accustomed to in Cove, but the long, tall, elegant birds thatseem to glide like paper in the wind.  It is beautiful.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Sometimes, the only way to describe paradies is to let it slide over yourbody like a cool satin sheet.  Take it all in, breathe it like it is air,and let it conquer you, let your body slip into one of those everlastingslumbers that only adventurers rarely experience.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Sometimes, words dont describe nor do they do justice to the meaning ofparadise.  And thats very nearly where you are at.  In fact, this is Elysia,the place of heroes, idols, and all those that find themselves fortunateenough to make their way here, people who have found a respite from theworlds troubles.

Small shelves clutter this tiny alcove of tree branches and artificallyplaced wood.  A tiny straw mat lies in the corner of the room, veryuncomfortable looking but certainly space saving.  The entire alcove is litonly by a small hooded lantern that hangs from a hook in the tree trunk.And overall, you'd have to say that you are not impressed with the abode onebit.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Beautiful waves of crystal water laps up on the whote sanded shore here,a vast expanse of water that stretches as far as your eyes can see.  But itis not as if you would want to leave this isle of trees and springs andwildlife.  It is the perfect respite of adventureres such as yourself.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Have you ever lies on the green grass behind your home, just staring upat the star filled sky, wondering who and what and why all those clustersand shapes of twinkling lights have been put there, why they have beenarranged just so, and what it all means?  Heroes have been carved into thenight line, men and women and immortals who will go down into history withthe best that any living being had to offer.  It was rumored that theseheroes have a resting place they like to come to once in a while, it wascalled Elysia, home of the brave and sanctimonious, the proud and the weary.And here you are on its shores, beautiful beyond belief, with everythinghere that you might want, were it not for your insatiable drive foradventure.

Rooms.EnterMsg: The warm sands part as $n steps onto the beach.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n strolls off to the $T.
Rooms.RoomDescription: Water creeps carefully to the white sanded shore here, a delicate balanceof nature that seems to have achieved harmony with such ease.  The waterfrom the vast expanse of ocean smells and looks drinkable, if you could tellthat much from the simple sight of it.  Trees on the island sway gently inthe seabreeze, fruit and meats magically hanging from their shade producingboughs.  Underfoot, when not standing on the warm sands of the beach, yourfeet are comforted by a thick mat of rolling green grass, perfect comfortand respite for your adventured out body.

Warm sap runs down the tree trunk that you have so elegantly scaled.  Itis a healthy tree, for lack of anything better to say, but what it DOESoffer you is a wonderful view of the forest ravine.  You can see how thetrail runs almost completely elliptical, a bubbling brook running throughits center, winding and curling in its clarity.  The fresh scent of pinehere is overwhelming, a true outdoor scent.

Pushing through the closely nestled trees whose branches entertwine toform a mural of almost impassable vegetation, you emerge into this clearingdevoid of brambles and snares.  The light shimmers down on the oddly shapedsilver pebbles surrounding this clearing, twisting and molding light infantastic formulations of beauty.  Your breath held, an anticipation ofsomething surreal gathers in your senses, forcing you pensive andintrospective.

Slowly, with breathless fragility, tendrils of life embrace you with therhythmic swaying of tree branches in the vibrant air.  Not content with youracquiesence to the power of nature surrounding you, the wind caresses younot so gently, eliciting a mortal reminder of subservience.  Thousands ofleagues from the herd, you feel the initially awkward yet invigoratingcomfort of being utterly alone.

Ironic that out here, in the middle of nowhere, amidst the hungry untamedbeasts, you feel safer than in the madness of the city.  Here in thispurity, animals abide by the laws of the jungle, logical and just.  From theinsanity of people comes the unfathomable ugliness that has corrupted knowncivilization so as to have sent you searching for just this type ofvividness.
